message.content: There is no way to know how many killers are left in the room just by knowing that someone has killed one of them. It could be any number between 2 and 3, depending on who was killed. If there were two killers and one person entered the room and killed one of them, then there would still be 2 killers left. If there were three killers and one person entered the room and killed one of them, there would also be 2 killers left.
